The conditional density of \( Y \) given \( X = x \) is \( f(y|x) = \frac{x + y}{x + 1} \) for \( 0 < y < 1 \). The conditional expectation \( E[Y|X=x] \) is then computed as \( \int_0^1 y \cdot \frac{x + y}{x + 1} \, dy = \frac{2x + 3}{2(3x + 1)} \).

